3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average of the premium/discount between the perpetual price and the mark price. The 8-hour TWAP is divided into 8 equal payments, creating more frequent but smaller funding exchanges compared to traditional 8-hour intervals. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while shorts receive payments, with settlements occurring automatically at the top of each hour."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","INJ","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"INJ/USDT presents compelling arbitrage opportunities due to Injective Protocol's role as a DeFi-focused blockchain with significant trading volume fluctuations. The pair often exhibits elevated funding rates during network upgrades, partnership announcements, or broader DeFi market movements, creating predictable patterns for sophisticated traders."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"INJ/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid typically range from -0.05% to 0.15% per 8-hour equivalent, with notable spikes during Injective ecosystem developments. The pair shows strong correlation with DeFi sector momentum, often maintaining positive funding during bull markets as retail traders prefer long exposure. Funding rates tend to normalize faster than on CEXs due to the 1-hour interval structure, reducing extreme rate persistence. Weekly patterns show elevated rates during US trading hours when DeFi activity peaks."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The 1-hour funding interval creates unique arbitrage windows, especially when rates diverge significantly from other exchanges like Binance or Bybit. Traders can exploit rate differences by taking opposing positions across exchanges, with Hyperliquid's fast settlement enabling quick position adjustments. Cross-DEX arbitrage becomes particularly profitable during INJ ecosystem events when retail sentiment drives funding premiums on centralized exchanges while Hyperliquid rates remain more balanced. The on-chain nature allows for programmatic execution without traditional API limitations."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's single-chain architecture concentrates smart contract risk, though the platform has demonstrated strong uptime since launch. USDC-only collateral limits hedging options compared to multi-asset margin systems, requiring careful position sizing for INJ's volatility. The newer exchange status means less historical data for pattern analysis, and liquidity can thin during extreme market conditions. Bridge risks exist when moving funds between Hyperliquid and other chains for cross-exchange arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are INJ/USDT funding rates paid on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding payments occur every hour at the top of the hour. The rate is calculated as 1/8th of the traditional 8-hour funding rate, providing more frequent but smaller payments compared to other exchanges."},{"question":"What makes Hyperliquid's INJ funding different from CEXs?","answer":"Hyperliquid's on-chain order book provides full transparency of funding rate calculations, while the 1-hour intervals create different arbitrage dynamics. The DEX structure also means no KYC requirements and direct wallet custody of positions."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage INJ funding between Hyperliquid and Binance?","answer":"Yes, rate differences between Hyperliquid and CEXs create arbitrage opportunities. However, you must account for bridge times, gas costs, and the different funding intervals when calculating potential profits."},{"question":"What's the maximum leverage for INJ/USDT on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Hyperliquid typically offers up to 20x leverage for INJ/USDT, though this can vary based on market conditions and position size. The platform uses cross-margin by default with isolated margin options available."}]}]
